Generic SHA-256 of any text input up to 55 bytes (single block).
Pads, packs into W[0..15] at runtime via byte_at, extends W[16..63]
inductively via sliding window during compression.
Output: i-th 32-bit word of the hash (which: 0..7).
Validated against sha256sum for multiple inputs.
helper rules: padded_byte, w_init, k_const.
compress is the recursive callable with W-window sliding.
sha256_word is the entry rule.
